.frame_delay
    LDX zp_frame_progress  \ Frame-rate regulator (busy-wait). Called once per main_loop iteration. zp_frame_progress accumulates 'work done this frame' (e.g. update_bullets does `INC zp_frame_progress` twice per active bullet, get_ready_overlay bumps it once per other frame). At entry, zp_frame_progress starts at zp_game_speed (set by the user's Speed option in `options.BAS` line 700: `?&92 = 120 + S%*30`, so 120 = slow .. 240 = fast; the BREAK cheat in Loader2 line 1310 sets it to 252). The busy loop runs (256 - X) outer iterations × 256-cycle inner loop, so the delay is INVERSELY proportional to zp_frame_progress: heavy frames (high X) get short delays, idle frames (X near zp_game_speed) get long delays — total frame time is roughly constant. The `CPX #&64 / BCS / LDX #&FE` guard handles the overflow case where so much work happened that zp_frame_progress wrapped past 255 to a small value (< 100): substitute X=&FE for a fixed minimum delay (~2 outer iterations) rather than the paradoxically-long (256-X) the underflowed value would imply. After the wait, zp_frame_progress is reset to zp_game_speed for the next frame.
    CPX #&64
    BCS L13C4
    LDX #&FE
.L13C4
    LDY #&00
.L13C6
    INY
    BNE L13C6
    INX
    BNE L13C4
    LDA zp_game_speed
    STA zp_frame_progress
    RTS

.game_step
    JSR try_spawn_pickup  \ ONE COLUMN of game progress — called once per main_loop iteration. Does the per-tile-column setup (try_spawn_pickup, spawn_periodic_hazard, spawn_check_step, then computes the new right-edge tile sprite pointers `zp_tile_lower_hi/lo` and `zp_tile_upper_hi/lo` by indexing `lev_map_lower[zp_scroll_col]` / `lev_map_upper[zp_scroll_col]` into the tile catalog at &4E80, multiply-by-&80 via repeated ADC), bumps `zp_scroll_col` by 1 (with wrap from &F0+ back to &F0 = the end-of-map loop), checks the PAUSE key, then runs 4 sub-frames (`play_subframe` loop, gated on `zp_get_ready_erase` going 0→1→2→3→4). Each subframe scrolls the playfield by 4 px (so 4×4 = 16 px = one tile-cell per game_step call), updates enemies / hazards / missiles / pickups, draws score, reads input, and on even columns also bumps `zp_frame_progress` + draws the get_ready overlay. Returns early once `lives_left` drops to 0, which the caller `main_loop` immediately tests to go to game_over_or_continue.
    JSR spawn_periodic_hazard
    JSR spawn_check_step
    LDX zp_scroll_col
    LDA lev_map_lower,X
    TAX
    INX
    LDA #&4E
    STA zp_tile_lower_hi
    LDA #&80
    STA zp_tile_lower_lo
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_dest_x_lo

.tile_lower_ptr_calc
    INC zp_dest_x_lo
    LDA zp_tile_lower_lo
    CLC
    ADC #&80
    STA zp_tile_lower_lo
    BNE tile_lower_ptr_advance
    INC zp_tile_lower_hi

.tile_lower_ptr_advance
    CPX zp_dest_x_lo
    BNE tile_lower_ptr_calc
    LDX zp_scroll_col
    LDA lev_map_upper,X
    TAX
    INX
    LDA #&4E
    STA zp_tile_upper_hi
    LDA #&80
    STA zp_tile_upper_lo
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_dest_x_lo

.tile_upper_ptr_calc
    INC zp_dest_x_lo
    LDA zp_tile_upper_lo
    CLC
    ADC #&80
    STA zp_tile_upper_lo
    BNE tile_upper_ptr_advance
    INC zp_tile_upper_hi

.tile_upper_ptr_advance
    CPX zp_dest_x_lo
    BNE tile_upper_ptr_calc
    INC zp_scroll_col
    LDA zp_scroll_col
    CMP #&F1
    BNE L142E
    LDA #&F0
    STA zp_scroll_col
.L142E
    LDX #KEY_PAUSE
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L1438
    JSR pause_game
.L1438
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_get_ready_erase

.play_subframe
    LDA lives_left  \ Body of game_step's per-subframe inner loop. Runs once per BBC display frame (gated by frame_delay). 4 iterations are run per game_step (= per tile-column of horizontal scroll), producing the 4-frame soft-scroll animation between successive columns.
    BEQ game_step_done
    JSR update_enemy_missiles
    JSR draw_score
    JSR force_pod_anim
    INC zp_get_ready_erase
    JSR frame_delay
    JSR update_hazards
    JSR scroll_step
    LDX #&00
    STX data_70FF
    INX
    STX zp_sprite_dir_flag
    JSR update_pickup
    JSR L15C4
    JSR read_input
    LDA zp_scroll_col
    AND #&01
    BNE play_subframe_tail
    INC zp_frame_progress
    JSR get_ready_overlay

.play_subframe_tail
    LDA zp_get_ready_erase
    CMP #&04
    BCC play_subframe

.game_step_done
    RTS

.draw_player
    LDX zp_player_x  \ Draw the player ship: plot lev_player_sprite (6×22 from &4E80 in LEVD1) at (zp_player_x, zp_player_y). If data_25A3 == 1 (force-pod power-up active), also call draw_player_pod at (player_x+5, player_y+1). Then JSR check_player_collisions and JMP to update_player_bullets.
    LDY zp_player_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&06
    LDY #&16
    LDA #LO(lev_player_sprite)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_player_sprite)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA data_25A3
    CMP #&01
    BNE L14AF
    LDA zp_player_x
    CLC
    ADC #&05
    TAX
    LDY zp_player_y
    INY
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #&39
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&04
    LDY #&18
    JSR draw_player_pod
.L14AF
    JSR check_player_collisions
    JMP update_bullets

.draw_player_pod
    LDA pod_anim_frame  \ Draw the player's force-pod (the rotating saucer that orbits the ship after a power-up). Selects one of three frames at gfx_pod_frame0/1/2 (&3900/&3960/&39C0) based on pod_anim_frame (= data_14D8, cycles 1/2/3 driven by vertical movement: move_player_down does INC, move_player_up does DEC, both wrap 1<->3). Falls through into sprite_plot_xy with X=4 byte-cols, Y=&18 lines.
    CMP #&01
    BEQ L14C8
    CMP #&02
    BEQ L14D0
    LDA #&C0
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L14C8
    LDA #&00
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JMP sprite_plot_xy
.L14D0
    LDA #&60
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JMP sprite_plot_xy

\ ----- data &14D8..&14D9 -----
.pod_anim_frame
    \ Force-pod animation frame (1 / 2 / 3). Selects which of the three gfx_pod_frame0/1/2 sprites draw_player_pod renders. Cycled by player vertical motion: each move_player_down INCs it (wraps 4→1), each move_player_up DECs it (wraps 0→3). Disk-initial value is 1.
    EQUB &01

\ ----- code &14D9..&1575 -----
.read_input
    LDA zp_9F  \ Read input: if joystick mode (zp_9F == 1) take read_joystick path; else scan KEY_RIGHT / KEY_LEFT / KEY_DOWN / KEY_UP / KEY_FIRE in turn via check_key_pressed and dispatch the matching move_player_* / on_fire_pressed routine.
    CMP #&01
    BEQ read_joystick
    LDX #KEY_RIGHT
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L14EC
    JSR move_player_right
    JMP L14F6
.L14EC
    LDX #KEY_LEFT
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L14F6
    JSR move_player_left
.L14F6
    LDX #KEY_DOWN
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L1500
    JSR move_player_down
.L1500
    LDX #KEY_UP
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L150A
    JSR move_player_up
.L150A
    LDX #KEY_FIRE
    JSR check_key_pressed
    BNE L1514
    JSR on_fire_pressed
.L1514
    JMP draw_player

.read_joystick
    LDA #&80  \ Read joystick: OSBYTE &80 reads analog joystick 1 X/Y axes (low/high thresholds &40/&C8) and the fire button bit, dispatching the same move_player_* / on_fire_pressed routines as the keyboard path.
    LDX #&01
    JSR OSBYTE
    CPY #&C8
    BCC L1528
    JSR move_player_left
    JMP L152F
.L1528
    CPY #&40
    BCS L152F
    JSR move_player_right
.L152F
    LDA #&80
    LDX #&02
    JSR OSBYTE
    CPY #&C8
    BCC L1540
    JSR move_player_down
    JMP L1547
.L1540
    CPY #&40
    BCS L1547
    JSR move_player_up
.L1547
    LDA #&80
    LDX #&00
    JSR OSBYTE
    TXA
    AND #&01
    CMP #&01
    BNE L1558
    JSR on_fire_pressed
.L1558
    JMP draw_player

.check_key_pressed
    LDA #&81  \ Wraps OSBYTE &81 (INKEY -X) for negative key scan. Returns Z=1 when the key whose internal code is in X is NOT pressed (Y was &FF), Z=0 when pressed. Callers use BNE = not pressed / BEQ = pressed.
    LDY #&FF
    JSR OSBYTE
    CPY #&FF
    RTS

.move_player_left
    LDA zp_player_x  \ Move player one column LEFT (DEC zp_player_x, clamped at min &02).
    CMP #&02
    BNE L156C
    RTS
.L156C
    DEC zp_player_x
    RTS
