    LDX #&09  \ Per-frame player collision check. Two loops: (a) X=8..1 over the hazard slots at hazard_x/_y/_state — for any slot whose hazard_state is in 1..9 (active), test the player against a 6×&18 bounding box; on hit, mark the slot &0A (expired) and JSR lose_a_life. (b) X=0..7 over the enemy slots (enemy_x, enemy_y, enemy_type < &14) — same test. Each hit triggers a `OSWRCH &07` (the BBC bell, redefined by Loader2 lines 5-9 via `*FX211..214` to be a short non-musical blip used as the in-game collision sound).
