\ ----- code &1A99..&1C12 -----
.hazard_try_fire_bullet
    JSR lfsr_random  \ Hazard 'try to fire a bullet' hook — called from update_hazards after plotting each active hazard slot. Random chance (rndval32 == 2 → 1/16) gates each call; further requires the hazard to be near the left edge (hazard_x < &10), the global cooldown zp_7E to be 0, and a free slot in enemy_bullet_x[4..1]. On success: stores hazard_x+2 / hazard_y-8 into the chosen slot, sets zp_7E = 8 (8-frame cooldown), plays sfx_hit_lo. Shares the enemy_bullet_x/_y pool with enqueue_enemy_bullet — hazards and enemies fire the same bullet sprite.
    LDA rndval32
    CMP #&02
    BEQ L1AA4
    RTS
.L1AA4
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CMP #&10
    BCC L1AAE
    JMP L1AAF
.L1AAE
    RTS
.L1AAF
    LDA zp_7E
    CMP #&00
    BEQ enemy_bullet_alloc
    RTS

.enemy_bullet_alloc
    LDX #&04
.L1AB8
    LDA enemy_bullet_x,X
    CMP #&FF
    BEQ L1AC3
    DEX
    BNE L1AB8
    RTS
.L1AC3
    STX data_16F6
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_x,X
    CLC
    ADC #&02
    LDX data_16F6
    STA enemy_bullet_x,X
    LDX data_16F5
    LDA hazard_y,X
    SEC
    SBC #&08
    LDX data_16F6
    STA enemy_bullet_y,X
    LDA #&08
    STA zp_7E
    JMP sfx_hit_lo

.update_hazards
    LDX #&08  \ Per-frame hazard update: iterate the 8 hazard slots (X=8..1 in hazard_state), move each by ±1 X / ±4 Y depending on data_16F6/16F7 direction bits, erase + redraw at the new position with a 4x24 sprite. Slot deactivates (and is erased) when hazard_state drops to 0. Hazards damage the player on contact (check_player_collisions) and are destructible by player bullets (check_bullet_hits).
