\ ----- data &2050..&208A -----
.player_hp
    \ Per-life HP — how many lose_a_life calls the current ship can absorb before it explodes. Reset to zp_9A by init (= zp_9A default 6, configurable from options.BAS as `?&9A = X%`). DEC'd in pairs by lose_a_life (every other call); when it hits 0 the next lose_a_life jumps to death_anim. Also used as the X-position of the lives icon in the bottom-status row (col player_hp + &1F).
    EQUB &06
.lives_left
    \ Lives counter — number of ships remaining BEFORE the current one (i.e. continues / extra lives). Initialised by restore_score_from_loader from loader_lives_save (= 3 at game start; preserved across levels). DEC'd by death_anim after the explosion plays. main_loop polls this each game_step: when it reaches 0 → JMP game_over_or_continue.
    EQUB &06
.enemy_x
    EQUB &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00
    EQUB &00, &EA
.enemy_y
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.enemy_type
    EQUB &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00, &00
    EQUB &00
.enemy_flip
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.enemy_hp
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA
.enemy_step
    EQUB &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA, &EA
    EQUB &EA, &EA

\ ----- code &208A..&23C5 -----
.spawn_check_step
    LDX zp_7B  \ Spawn-table scanner — runs once per frame from main_loop. Compares lev_spawn_col[zp_7B] against zp_scroll_col; on match, decodes the paired lev_spawn_attr byte into a new enemy in the slot pool: bits 0..4 → enemy_type (0..31), bit 7 → enemy_flip (INVERTED: 0 in attr = upright, 1 = vertical-flip), bits 5..6 → spawn row 0..3 mapped to Y = &DF / &BF / &9F / &7F (4 evenly-spaced lines spanning the playfield gap between the upper and lower tile bands). Initial slot state: enemy_x = &28 (off-screen right, col 40), enemy_hp = &14 for type &10 / &06 for types &07 and < &03 / &08 otherwise, enemy_step = 4. Allocates slot via zp_7C (round-robin 0..7). On any non-spawning type (3..6 special-cased) it re-enters spawn_check_step to drain back-to-back spawns at the same column.
    LDA lev_spawn_col,X
    CMP zp_scroll_col
    BEQ L2094
    RTS
.L2094
    LDA lev_spawn_attr
    BNE L209A
    RTS
.L209A
    INC zp_7C
    LDA zp_7C
    CMP #&08
    BCC L20A6

.tbl_20A2
    LDA #&00
    STA zp_7C
.L20A6
    INC zp_7B
    LDA lev_spawn_attr,X
    TAY
    LDX zp_7C
    AND #&1F
    STA enemy_type,X
    TYA
    AND #&80
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    EOR #&01
    STA enemy_flip,X
    TYA
    AND #&60
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    LSR A
    TAX
    INX
    LDA #&FF
    SEC
.L20CF
    SBC #&20
    DEX
    BNE L20CF
    LDX zp_7C
    STA enemy_y,X
    LDA #&28
    STA enemy_x,X
    LDA #&08
    STA enemy_hp,X
    LDA #&04
    STA enemy_step,X
    LDA enemy_type,X
    CMP #&10
    BEQ L20FA
    CMP #&07
    BEQ L2102
    CMP #&03
    BCC L2102
    JMP spawn_check_step
.L20FA
    LDA #&14
    STA enemy_hp,X
    JMP spawn_check_step
.L2102
    LDA #&06
    STA enemy_hp,X
    JMP spawn_check_step

.update_enemies
    LDA forcefield_active  \ Per-frame enemy + force-field update + plot. First clears the force-field strip if forcefield_active=1 (erases a 2×&20 rectangle at (forcefield_x, forcefield_y) and clears the flag — the strip is procedural noise re-drawn every frame, so it has to be wiped before forcefield_render generates a fresh one). Then iterates the 8 enemy slots: for each active enemy (enemy_type != 0), DEC enemy_x to scroll it left, redraw, and dispatch any per-type behaviour via enemy_type_dispatch.
    CMP #&01
    BNE L2130
    LDX forcefield_x
    LDY forcefield_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&02
    LDY #&20
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    LDA #&00
    STA forcefield_active
