.spawn_flame
    LDA flame_state  \ Spawn the flame projectile. Called from enemy_type_dispatch when an enemy of type 8 wants to fire. Refuses if `flame_state != 0` (only one flame at a time) or if the firing enemy's `enemy_x < &0C` (it has already scrolled too far left to spawn from). On success: mutates the firing enemy to type 9 (the post-fire idle state), copies its position into `flame_x` / `flame_y` (with a per-flip Y offset), and sets `flame_state = 1` to start the 6-frame animation.
    BEQ L246A
    RTS
.L246A
    LDA enemy_x,X
    CMP #&0C
    BCS L2472
    RTS
.L2472
    LDA #&09
    STA enemy_type,X
    LDA enemy_y,X
    LDY enemy_flip,X
    SEC
    CPY #&01
    BNE L2487
    SBC #&08
    JMP L2489
.L2487
    SBC #&10
.L2489
    STA flame_y
    LDA enemy_x,X
    SBC #&09
    STA flame_x
    LDA #&01
    STA flame_state
    RTS

.flame_x
    NOP  \ Flame projectile X coord — column. DEC'd by 1 per call to update_flame so the flame drifts left through the playfield as the scenery scrolls. When it falls below &02 the flame deactivates (off-screen left).

.flame_y
    NOP  \ Flame projectile Y coord (in scanlines).

.flame_state
    BRK  \ Flame state machine: 0 = inactive (slot free for a new spawn); 1..6 = animation frames (1=&3B00, 2=&3B40, 3=&3B80, then ping-pongs back 4=&3B80, 5=&3B40, 6=&3B00); 7 = deactivate next call. Each call to update_flame INCs the state (via advance_flame_state) or jumps straight to 7 if the player has been hit.

.update_flame
    LDX flame_x  \ Per-frame flame update (called from update_enemies when `flame_state != 0`). Erases the previous 32×8 frame, shifts the flame left by 1 px (DEC flame_x), then either re-plots the next animation frame from `gfx_flame_frame0..2` (states 1..6) or deactivates (state 7 / off-screen). Each frame is 8 byte-cols × 8 lines = 32×8 px. There is only ever one flame on screen — `spawn_flame` checks `flame_state` and refuses to start a new one until this slot is free.
    LDY flame_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDA #LO(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    LDA #HI(lev_erase_brush + &80)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDX #&08
    LDY #&08
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    DEC flame_x
    LDA flame_x
    CMP #&02
    BCS plot_flame
    JMP deactivate_flame

.plot_flame
    TAX  \ Plot the flame at its updated position. Dispatches by `flame_state` to one of three frame plotters: state 1/6 → `plot_flame_frame_0` (`gfx_flame_frame0` at &3B00), state 2/5 → `plot_flame_frame_1` (`gfx_flame_frame1` at &3B40), state 3/4 → `plot_flame_frame_2` (`gfx_flame_frame2` at &3B80). State 7 → `deactivate_flame`.
    LDY flame_y
    JSR calc_screen_addr
    LDX #&08
    LDY #&08
    LDA #HI(gfx_flame_frame0)
    STA sprite_src_hi
    LDA flame_state
    CMP #&01
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_0
    CMP #&02
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_1
    CMP #&03
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_2
    CMP #&04
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_2
    CMP #&05
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_1
    CMP #&06
    BEQ plot_flame_frame_0
    CMP #&07
    BEQ deactivate_flame
    BNE plot_flame_frame_0
    RTS

.plot_flame_frame_0
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame0)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.plot_flame_frame_1
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame1)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.plot_flame_frame_2
    LDA #LO(gfx_flame_frame2)
    STA sprite_src_lo
    JSR sprite_plot_xy
    JMP flame_collide_player

.deactivate_flame
    LDA #&00  \ Deactivate the flame — `flame_state = 0`. Reached when the flame has reached its final animation frame, drifts off the left edge, or has hit the player.
    STA flame_state
    LDX data_16F5
    RTS

.flame_collide_player
    LDA flame_x  \ Box-test the flame against the player. Collision box is offset (+4, -4) from the plotted position, 6 px wide × &18 (24) lines tall. On hit: set `flame_state = 7` (so the next call deactivates) and JMP `lose_a_life`.
    CLC
    ADC #&04
    STA zp_test_x
    LDA flame_y
    SEC
    SBC #&04
    STA zp_test_y
    LDA zp_player_x
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCS advance_flame_state
    ADC #&06
    CMP zp_test_x
    BCC advance_flame_state
    LDA zp_player_y
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCC advance_flame_state
    SBC #&18
    CMP zp_test_y
    BCS advance_flame_state
    LDA #&07
    STA flame_state
    JMP lose_a_life

.advance_flame_state
    INC flame_state  \ Tail of `flame_collide_player` for the no-hit case — INC `flame_state` so the next frame plots the next animation step (1→2→3→4→5→6→7→deactivate).
    RTS

